ğŸ”¹ Problem: Rotate Array (Medium)
ğŸ”¹ Approach Used: Extra Space (Using Temp Array)
ğŸ” Concepts: Array Rotation, Modulo, Vectors

ğŸ’¡ Problem Brief:
Given an integer array nums, rotate the array to the right by k steps, where k is non-negative.

âœ… Approach Explanation: We create a temporary array and use (i + k) % n to place each element in its new position.


void rotate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<int> temp(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        temp[(i + k) % n] = nums[i];
    }
    nums = temp;
}


==> This method ensures all elements are rotated correctly with time complexity O(n) and space complexity O(n).
